Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.50,0:00:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Along with the yearly visit of the fresh summer breeze,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.04,0:00:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from Okinawa archipelago, India,\Nand New Guinea, comes to Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.13,0:00:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a bird, whose song announces the beginning of summer...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.34,0:00:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the cuckoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.39,0:00:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, cuckoo! Should we simply call you "a bird,"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.89,0:00:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or should we call you "a wandering voice"?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.06,0:00:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As many people indeed know, this\Nbird is best known for its song.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.85,0:00:28.86,cuckoo,,0000,0000,0000,,Cuckoo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.27,0:00:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it is also known for its peculiar reproductive habits.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.82,0:00:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She stalks, silently, behind buntings'\Nand great reed warblers' nests,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.74,0:00:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when she sees that the parents have left the nest,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.20,0:00:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she flies there quickly and deposits her own egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.88,0:00:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, she doesn't forget to\Neliminate one of the owner's eggs,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.50,0:00:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that the number of eggs in the nest remains unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.26,0:00:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a super quick technique, taking\Nonly ten seconds, and there's more!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.59,0:01:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once the little bird breaks the shell and emerges from\Nhis egg, he pushes the other eggs out of the nest...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.60,0:01:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to monopolize the food that the adopted\Nmother bird will bring to the nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.77,0:01:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a terrific natural instinct!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.44,0:01:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can definitely say that the fate of a mother,\Nexploited by her offspring, is awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.53,0:01:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, we cannot even imagine the unbearable\Npain the mother bird must go through,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.41,0:01:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,waiting for the day in which the enemy\Nof her own chicks will be able to fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.91,0:01:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the mother bird, having never seen\Nher chick, departs for the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.30,0:01:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But a son is always a son, and so is a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.68,0:01:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite what happened, she wishes all the best for the son.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.01,0:01:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Separating from a son is always painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.30,0:01:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are birds who fly towards the dusk together with their\Nsons, and birds, like the albatross, who separate from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.81,0:01:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Poor little me, orphaned and abandoned without\Na land, in the middle of rivers and mountains..."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.40,0:01:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"In this life, as short as a dewdrop... No! I don't have to cry!"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.15,0:01:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coo-coooo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.74,0:02:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps this is what the cuckoo was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.87,0:02:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't really know, because I'm\Nnot a bird, but this is his story!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.63,0:02:25.10,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,I watch the sky through the keyhole, and\Nwhat I see is a person's silhouette
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.81,0:02:31.69,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my casual encounter with a tomorrow I've never seen
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.02,0:02:37.48,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Outer space always starts from an interphone
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.24,0:02:44.03,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, one step out, and I find the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.37,0:02:49.91,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no armor to protect the family
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.58,0:02:57.38,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,The only weapon to search for our roots is consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.96,0:03:07.22,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,If only you had love, dreams, and frontiers...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.14,0:03:19.03,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Lineage, the road home, heritage, and\Norigins depend on space and time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.49,0:03:27.33,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,The wife has the household, the servant, and the genealogy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.45,0:03:32.46,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Transcend and run through the time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.33,0:03:38.63,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Long long life to the ancestors!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.85,0:05:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you see something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.64,0:05:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A yellow flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.31,0:05:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or at least, I thought I saw one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.94,0:05:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A yellow flower?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.73,0:05:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I thought I saw, but now I can't see it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.78,0:05:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was never there,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.57,0:05:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I just had a feeling that it was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.03,0:05:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.37,0:05:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... how the hell should I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.67,0:05:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously, you can't know. The one\Nwho saw it was me, {\i1}not{\i0} you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.25,0:05:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consequently, this is a problem for you to solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.70,0:06:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, today is a such a beautiful day!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.99,0:06:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.45,0:06:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a really fantastic day!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.29,0:06:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The clouds float in the sky, and the sun illuminates\Nthe goldenrod as it waves gently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.83,0:06:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this time, after a long winter, the girls\Ndowntown finally take off their coats.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.84,0:06:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and show brilliant smiles while window shopping,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.17,0:06:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,waiting for a brilliant young boy to give them the word.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.55,0:06:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can even hear their bright laughing\Nvoices, seeming to invite me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.18,0:06:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, why don't you go out too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.98,0:06:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad and Mom won't mind at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.23,0:06:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.65,0:06:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not falling for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.61,0:06:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Inumaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.95,0:06:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not typical of you. You don't have to worry about-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.20,0:06:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.54,0:06:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this morning, when I went to the bathroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:07:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, right? When I stole your turn, as usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.21,0:07:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understood when I saw you in your baggy pants,\Nwith the huge Sunday paper under your arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.88,0:07:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ah! Today, Dad wants to lie down\Nand take it easy, all day long!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.01,0:07:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru, you know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.47,0:07:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.35,0:07:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You work late every day. You're tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.97,0:07:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, at least on Sunday, you want to\Ndo whatever you like, like lie down,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.85,0:07:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,fart, watch boring TV sports shows, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.56,0:07:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, to free your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.44,0:07:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're old, lazy, and could be called a pack of rubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.99,0:07:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l know that myself! But I won't allow anyone else to say so!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, this morning, when I opened\Nmy eyes in bed, I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.29,0:07:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"For me, it's a day like any other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.54,0:07:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But for Daddy, it's a special day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.75,0:07:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the day I have to do everything I can possibly\Ndo to make messes and disturb him."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.38,0:07:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I left home like a young\Nman who'd decided to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.76,0:07:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that Daddy would be really happy\Nto receive a present on a day like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.77,0:08:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, why didn't you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.69,0:08:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I wanted to do, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.52,0:08:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have my allowance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.98,0:08:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a cent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.07,0:08:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you have any money?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.90,0:08:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The month has just started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.95,0:08:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, yesterday, near the station, I spotted\Na men's Bighi pullover for this beautiful season.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.54,0:08:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should've seen its wonderful color!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.41,0:08:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An exact shining yellow, just like the goldenrod\Nthat blossoms in this season!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.34,0:08:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so you bought it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.05,0:08:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I didn't have 28,000 yen in my pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.26,0:08:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, it would've been useless to ask Mom,\Nand I knew you'd have refused as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.76,0:08:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I went to the sporting goods store and\Nused every cent I had to buy this metal bat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.05,0:09:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru, since you were a kid, you've\Nalways been a kind-hearted boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.05,0:09:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't the type to raise your hands\Nto others, even if you were the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.05,0:09:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, even I, your father, got somewhat upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.35,0:09:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I knew how it would end up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.27,0:09:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, the young angel would reveal his violent instincts,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.73,0:09:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and would turn into a monster, in front of my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.90,0:09:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I bought one too, Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.82,0:09:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that sporting goods store near the\Nboutique in front of the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.79,0:09:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This metal-faced driver!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.91,0:09:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old-timer in the shop said to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like a diabolic tempter, he whispered\Nto me that with its devastating power,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.80,0:09:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this metal-faced driver would beat any metal bat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.30,0:10:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, I somewhat regret having\Nmade this driver into a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.51,0:10:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you know the reason, don't you, Inumaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.97,0:10:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its head will bend with the impact!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.10,0:10:17.54,Family,,0000,0000,0000,,Yomota
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.08,0:10:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The doorbell rang, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.58,0:10:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That indeed appears to be so, Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.92,0:10:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.13,0:10:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darling, what are you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.30,0:10:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, nothing. A crisis had just begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.68,0:10:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.18,0:10:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who on earth could be here at this time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.52,0:10:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darling, sorry, but would you mind going to open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.56,0:10:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, yesterday I kept really long\Nhours, and I'm still like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.99,0:10:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru! Inumaru! You're not home?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.90,0:11:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Mom. Beautiful day, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.33,0:11:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.16,0:11:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do me a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.16,0:11:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see. Daddy and I are still like this, so go open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.25,0:11:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I'm "still like this" too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.13,0:11:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How persistent! I'm fed up! Who is it already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.84,0:11:24.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's a colleague from work?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.39,0:11:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this time on a Sunday?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.77,0:11:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A friend of yours, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.27,0:11:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not expecting anyone. Could it be a neighbor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.94,0:11:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know how I hate to deal with neighbors!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.27,0:11:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we moved here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.11,0:11:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't they stop already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.70,0:11:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least on Sunday, leave us in peace!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.87,0:11:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.37,0:11:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going immediately. I'm going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.38,0:11:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru! Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.63,0:12:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's a salesman or a religious mission,\Nrefuse at once! Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.39,0:12:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And even those NHK toll collectors!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.81,0:12:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it? Can you see something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.60,0:12:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A flower. I see a yellow flower!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.06,0:12:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A yellow flower? Didn't you say you simply imagined it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.94,0:12:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see it clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A flower. A yellow flower!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.21,0:12:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it, Inumaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.80,0:12:45.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand what type of attitude you should show?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.47,0:12:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Mom, I got it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.43,0:12:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never open that door!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.22,0:12:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even before that, you shouldn't fall for\Nthe urges of an impulsive curiosity!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.98,0:13:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although the girl you can see through the\Npeephole looks beautiful and honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.53,0:13:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,although the voice from the intercom echoes like an angel,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.24,0:13:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you mustn't fall into the trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.74,0:13:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those people would do just about\Nanything to get the door opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.75,0:13:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And once they get it open, just like a Navy attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.66,0:13:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they will pass through their enemies\Nand gain access to the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.54,0:13:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will push forward with all their\Nstrength and won't retreat a step!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.51,0:13:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.80,0:13:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't show the slightest welcome, and\Nkeep yourself on maximum alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.39,0:13:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to show your personality!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.93,0:13:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, display an anonymous coldness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.81,0:13:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.27,0:13:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without incurring their hate or anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.86,0:13:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,calmly, but stubbornly...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.03,0:13:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry that you came here, but come another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.07,0:13:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.24,0:13:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.04,0:13:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However... what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.37,0:13:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, from this little peephole.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.62,0:14:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see a yellow flower, more winning than any smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.54,0:14:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whisper I hear from the intercom feels like...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.13,0:14:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the wind coming to the beautiful plains of goldenrod.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.55,0:14:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.55,0:14:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.22,0:14:15.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understood, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.02,0:14:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is pure fantasy... nothing more than a child's dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.32,0:14:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like earlier, when I spotted that\Nyellow flower from the veranda,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.86,0:14:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it disappeared when I tried to look more carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.95,0:14:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,together with hope, at the limit of desperation!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.37,0:14:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I opened this door,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.16,0:14:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all I'd find would certainly be a yakuza, with\Nhis permed hair and menacing power,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.16,0:14:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who would do anything to sell me a subscription\Nto some weird yakuza magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.09,0:14:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe someone who's collecting\Nsigns or funds for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.72,0:14:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or someone involved in a popular action movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If worst comes to worst, it might\Nbe a girl come from a far land
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.85,0:14:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the other side of this door, in order to spread\Ndestruction and devastation on this family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.69,0:15:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.81,0:15:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm gonna regret it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.07,0:15:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.74,0:15:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pointless to wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.32,0:15:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially while continuing to act out\Na trite comedy like the one were in!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.91,0:15:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I continue waiting for the story of my love, it'll never start!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.46,0:15:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't open this door,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.58,0:15:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my tale may never take place!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.46,0:15:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my! But what the hell are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.30,0:15:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I wanted to explain it, it would\Nonly be a desperate attempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.51,0:15:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying that I don't intend to be a secondary\Ncharacter in this hoary tale,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.97,0:15:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the real protagonist of the story of my life instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.65,0:15:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why... that's why I wanted to go out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.03,0:15:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On Sunday in such wonderful weather!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.24,0:15:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To that street beyond the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.49,0:15:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I absolutely needed that pullover to do so!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.33,0:15:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, at the boutique in front of the station, I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.87,0:16:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that men's Bighi spring type pullover.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.79,0:16:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a wonderful color it had!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.54,0:16:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gorgeous bright yellow pullover, perfect\Nfor the blossoming of the goldenrod.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.01,0:16:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only I could've put it on and gone downtown, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.01,0:16:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could've become the protagonist of my story!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.77,0:16:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,28,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.02,0:16:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just because I didn't have that money,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.81,0:16:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up buying that metal bat, in the sporting\Ngoods store nearby, paying every cent I had.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.99,0:16:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite all this, my father bought a metal-faced driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.45,0:16:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, in that store,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.12,0:16:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the same diabolical old timer, in that sporting goods\Nstore next to the boutique, keeping it hidden away...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.21,0:16:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now everything is lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.50,0:16:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... You don't understand anything about my feelings!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.22,0:16:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do it, Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.77,0:17:11.86,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Note: "Gosenzosama" means "honorable ancestor."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.77,0:17:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gosenzosama!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.04,0:17:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... excuse me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.92,0:17:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Err, excuse me... One moment... Wha...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.49,0:18:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.78,0:18:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a damn playboy, my son!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.29,0:18:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A simple high school student who has not an illegitimate\Ndaughter, but rather a granddaughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.66,0:18:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a delinquent! How shameless!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.58,0:18:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, it's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.17,0:18:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? You'd play the fool? You ungrateful piece of...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.17,0:18:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard what she said, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.30,0:18:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Yomota Marako.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.80,0:18:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's name is Inumaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.60,0:18:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's father's name is Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.77,0:18:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, Grandfather Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.14,0:18:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your granddaughter, Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.65,0:18:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.27,0:18:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a false accusation!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.69,0:18:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop making malicious hypotheses\Nbased upon distasteful jokes. Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.86,0:18:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Given her age, it's much more reasonable that she's your\Nillegitimate daughter than my illegitimate granddaughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.74,0:18:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't know anything about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.37,0:18:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Yomota Marako.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.45,0:18:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's name is Inumaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.08,0:18:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's father's name is Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.13,0:18:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His father's name is Kinekuni.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.88,0:18:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.46,0:18:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it? Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.26,0:18:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at what? And anyway, how old is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.68,0:19:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my time, 17 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.14,0:19:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can I have a 17 year old granddaughter if I'm only 17?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.06,0:19:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's something even a kid would understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.18,0:19:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.31,0:19:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're my father, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.44,0:19:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're an adult, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.27,0:19:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the Yomota family leader, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.73,0:19:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if you're the leader, act like one,\Nand take responsibility for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.49,0:19:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leader? I'm only a,leader in my sub-branch at work!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.99,0:19:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only when I'm at work do I have to solve\Nproblems arid take responsibility!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.95,0:19:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our Yomota family has already jumped into the\Nmiddle of some mutation of ordinary life!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.46,0:19:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, the boring family drama of our lives is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.04,0:19:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, a new story begins,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.17,0:19:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where even parents' and son's wills collide with each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.17,0:19:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,leaving forever a life at the limit of humanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.05,0:19:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You piece of...! You think this is fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.18,0:19:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're having fun, aren't you? Aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.35,0:19:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I understood you, Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.77,0:19:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is some low class drama you organized!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.06,0:19:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she's just some loose girl you dragged\Nin from the street, isn't she?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.48,0:19:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't distance yourself by covering\Nme with crap like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.90,0:19:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every day, you keep repeating that you're\Nthe boss. Now act like one already!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.20,0:20:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.11,0:20:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.82,0:20:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.66,0:20:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.28,0:20:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.95,0:20:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.53,0:20:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.78,0:20:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out already!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.53,0:20:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouting in each others faces is just a waste of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.75,0:20:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one way to put an end to all this confusion\Nand to verify the truth, and I'm gonna take care of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.88,0:20:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are just four possibilities to explain the identity\Nof this girl, who says she's Inumaru's granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.88,0:20:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.84,0:20:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,its a joke organized by Inumaru and his girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.14,0:20:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that was the case, we'd have called\Nher Dad's illegitimate daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.81,0:20:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.89,0:20:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad decided to present his illegitimate daughter\Nas his illegitimate granddaughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.56,0:20:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, I'd have come up with a more realistic excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.73,0:20:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Third,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.52,0:20:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this girl is a *bip*!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.78,0:20:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a *bip*!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.19,0:20:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fourth,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.99,0:20:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she's a swindler who wants to infiltrate our home and\Nsteal our fortune by pretending to be a descendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.32,0:20:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? What fortune are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.49,0:20:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We only have a mortgage to pay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.62,0:20:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she's a swindler, she'd have chosen\Na more believable story!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.04,0:20:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... my granddaughter! Granddaughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.09,0:21:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Yomota Marako.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.17,0:21:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's name is Inumaro,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.67,0:21:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his father's name is Inumaru,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.59,0:21:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and his father's name is Kinekuni!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.22,0:21:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came here in a time machine I rented in my era,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.26,0:21:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I traveled back 30 years in order\Nto see my ancestors at least once!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.06,0:21:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you even mention this possibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.52,0:21:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to exclude it, please tell\Nme your reasons for doing so!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.40,0:21:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she's not completely wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.70,0:21:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to include it as a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.28,0:21:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least, that's logical.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.29,0:21:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How foolish!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.66,0:21:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you believe that time machine story?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.04,0:21:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's a hypothesis, it's no different than\Nbelieving in Dad's illegitimate daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.17,0:21:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're talking about possibilities,\Nwe have to consider it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.09,0:21:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you start listing the possibilities?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.51,0:21:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't use the word "possibility'' without any distinctions!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.60,0:21:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to consider common sense and logic!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.73,0:21:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time machine means time leap... and this\Ncinematic scenario isn't realistic at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.73,0:22:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And anyway it doesn't fit a family drama like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.49,0:22:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't allow it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.62,0:22:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.16,0:22:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.16,0:22:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's stipulate your version...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.62,0:22:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.04,0:22:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,two,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.41,0:22:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,three!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.58,0:22:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FourFiveSixSevenEightNine...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.71,0:22:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hundred steps of advantage!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.55,0:22:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's also stipulate that you're a Yomota descendant.\Ncome from the future in a time machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.18,0:22:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you have to prove to us that it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.98,0:22:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't do that, you'll have to leave immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.52,0:22:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that okay with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.44,0:22:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.61,0:22:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If It was the past, or the present, still...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.61,0:22:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's impossible to prove something\Nthat hasn't happened yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.53,0:22:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna fall into the trap of "your" logic!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.45,0:22:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're all good at talking!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.78,0:22:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't prove it, then give us some evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.08,0:22:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.79,0:23:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irrefutable evidence that you've come from the future...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.59,0:23:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.96,0:23:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.42,0:23:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! The time machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.97,0:23:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This fatal time machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.81,0:23:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.10,0:23:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The famous time machine that brought you here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.40,0:23:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time machine that brought me here...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.94,0:23:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The machine that overcame the flow\Nof time and brought me here...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.78,0:23:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.22,0:23:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.47,0:23:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Miss! Stop lying, already!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.02,0:24:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can that airship be a time machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.44,0:24:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a law that time travelers must never break:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.86,0:24:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,namely, never introduce changes in\Nthe past that change the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.74,0:24:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We call this "the principle of non-intervention in history."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.62,0:24:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, in order to protect the past from the future,\Nthe machine must remain hidden,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.54,0:24:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in an unrecognizable form.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.13,0:24:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may take different shapes that enable it\Nto hide in the background of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.96,0:24:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes it flies slowly in the sky, colored yellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.38,0:24:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Other times...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.43,0:24:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.55,0:24:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who would ever believe these tricks!\NNow speak seriously already!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.85,0:24:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have! I have one bit of evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.10,0:24:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Evidence that you can see and even touch with your hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.60,0:24:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... if I let you see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.23,0:24:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will you allow me to stay in this house with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.53,0:24:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A housewife has only one word!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.91,0:25:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's this!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.17,0:25:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the irrefutable evidence\Nthat she's part of the Yomota!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.55,0:25:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A five-pointed star shape!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.19,0:25:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.15,0:25:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The five-pointed star shape is transmitted\Nonly through Yomota family members!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.61,0:25:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's evidence that shows I'm part of the Yomota\Nfamily, and it doesn't vanish with age!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.32,0:25:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Yomota Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.66,0:25:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's name is Inumaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.45,0:25:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His father's name is Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.83,0:25:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His father's name is Kinekuni!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.58,0:25:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you! Grandfather! Great grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.88,0:25:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your granddaughter, Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.09,0:25:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your great granddaughter, Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.42,0:25:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.76,0:25:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.26,0:26:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chase that girl out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.76,0:26:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't do that, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.43,0:26:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will leave this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.10,0:26:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.57,0:26:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This girl is a Yomota.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.65,0:26:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's part of our family!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.57,0:26:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try to understand it!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.04,0:26:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For a birthmark on the derriere...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.95,0:26:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, who have been by your side for\Nyears, and given you a son...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.92,0:26:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would never have thought I'd lose\Nto a birthmark on a derriere...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.00,0:26:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.42,0:26:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Inumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.80,0:26:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out for evil girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.35,0:26:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.93,0:26:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of yourself, and don't drink too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.27,0:26:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty years spent in this family...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.52,0:26:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And even if I'm lnumaru's mother and your wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.95,0:27:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never achieved becoming a Yomota.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.16,0:27:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not leaving because I'm being chased out, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.71,0:27:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a woman, as Hakkoda Tamiko,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.08,0:27:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I choose to leave this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.88,0:27:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll certainly be back...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.17,0:27:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to take you and Inumaru back... to\Nfight for the Yomota household.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.76,0:27:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru... and you, dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.48,0:27:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.94,0:27:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we have to separate!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.50,0:28:16.42,Gosenzo,,0000,0000,0000,,Long long life to the ancestors!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.80,0:28:23.60,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(200,340)\fad(1300,1300)}An evil woman breaks\Ninto the household.
